## 2. Calculate mean % relative abundance by compartment, using pipe

you need to mutate data by making a percent column (multiply Abundance
values by 100). Then a summarise statement to calculate the mean
percentage. In order to group this by Compartment, you need to add a
group_by statement prior to the mutate statement.

``` r
microbiome.subset %>%
  group_by(Compartment) %>%
  mutate(Percent=Abundance*100) %>%
  summarise(Mean=mean(Percent)) %>% 
  
  head()
```

    ## # A tibble: 2 Ã— 2
    ##   Compartment   Mean
    ##   <chr>        <dbl>
    ## 1 Leaf        0.0409
    ## 2 Root        0.0409

now, you are given means for root and leaf compartments.

## 6. Calculate standard error for each mean in question 5

Add in a calculation for standard deviation in the summarise function,
and then use it in another muatation calculating a column for standard
error.

**I used the second example where Order is by itself in the group_by()

microbiome.subset %>%

  mutate(Percent=Abundance*100) %>%
  summarise(Mean=mean(Percent),

## 7. Select columms, pivot data to wide so that compartment are column headers

to make the data wide formatm use pivot_wider(): **I used the names from
Compartment, and the values from Mean, so that the mean values for each
order were in separate columns titled â€œleafâ€ and â€œrootâ€.**

``` r
microbiome.subset %>%
  filter(Class=="Dothideomycetes") %>%
  group_by(Order,Compartment,Fungicide) %>%
  mutate(Percent=Abundance*100) %>%
  summarise(Mean=mean(Percent),
            n=n(),
            stddev=sd(Percent)) %>%
  mutate(stderr=stddev/sqrt(n)) %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from=Compartment,values_from=Mean)
```

## 8. recreate the given plot from question 7 dataset

I need to add the ggplot function and layers, and I also need to reorder
the y axis.

``` r
microbiome.subset %>%
  filter(Class=="Dothideomycetes") %>%
  group_by(Order,Compartment,Fungicide) %>%
  mutate(Percent=Abundance*100) %>%
  mutate(Order2=fct_reorder(Order,desc(Percent))) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=Percent,y=Order2,fill=Fungicide,color=Fungicide))+
  stat_summary(fun=mean,geom="bar",position="dodge")+
  ylab("Order")+
  xlab("Percent relative abundance")
```
